==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rietboc
<hw>Riet"boc</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D. <ets>riet</ets>
reed + <ets>bok</ets> buck.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The reedbuck,
a South African antelope (<spn>Cervicapra arundinacea</spn>); -- so
called from its frequenting dry places covered with high grass or reeds.
Its color is yellowish brown. Called also <altname>inghalla</altname>,
and <altname>rietbok</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

